    <item>
      <title>Setup DHCP Client with systemd-networkd</title>
      <link>https://blog.pseudocold.com/post/2019/setup-dhcp-systemd-networkd/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 15 Oct 2019 17:19:31 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.pseudocold.com/post/2019/setup-dhcp-systemd-networkd/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Former package group &amp;ldquo;base&amp;rdquo; from Archlinux contains 2 network managers - &lt;code&gt;netctl&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;systemd-networkd&lt;/code&gt;, and 1 DHCP client &lt;code&gt;dhcpcd&lt;/code&gt;, which is obviously redundant for a network setup. After &lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.pseudocold.com/post/2019/base-group-replaced-by-mandatory-base-package-in-archlinux&#34;&gt;pkg group &amp;ldquo;base&amp;rdquo; replaced by the same name meta pkg&lt;/a&gt;, only &lt;code&gt;systemd-networkd&lt;/code&gt; is left. For a simple network setup with DHCP, &lt;code&gt;systemd-networkd&lt;/code&gt; is enough to get the work done.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Migrate from base Group Package to Meta Pkg in Archlinux</title>
